content: "It is surely the pursuit of peace that is most needed in this world so full of strife." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "As members of Congress reflect on their pending decision, I urge them to set aside political considerations.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "As Americans, we should be proud of this achievement." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "Now we have before us a solution that prevents Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon without resorting to war." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "President Kennedy warned Americans not to see conflict as inevitable. It is time to apply such wisdom.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "I have repeatedly challenged anyone opposed to this deal to put forward a better, plausible alternative." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "When we carefully examine the arguments against this deal, none of them stand up to scrutiny.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "If Iran violates this deal, we will have ample opportunity to respond." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "Worry less about being labeled weak. Worry more about getting it right.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "How can we in good conscience justify war before we have tested a diplomatic agreement that achieves our objectives?" â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: â€œThe choice we face is ultimately between diplomacy or some sort of war.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: â€œWalk away from this agreement and you will get a better dealâ€”for Iran.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: â€œThose who say we can walk away from this deal and maintain sanctions are selling a fantasy.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "We will continue to have sanctions in place on Iran's support for terrorism and violation of human rights."â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: â€œThere is no scenario where sanctions relief turns Iran into the region's dominate power.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: â€œAn argument against sanctions relief is effectively an argument against any diplomatic solution.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "Without this deal, the scenarios that critics warn about happening in 15 years could happen six months from now." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "The bottom line is, if Iran cheats, we can catch themâ€”and we will." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: â€œThis deal is not just the best choice among alternativesâ€”this is the strongest non-proliferation agreement ever.â€ â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: â€œIf Iran violates the agreement over the next decade all of the sanctions can snap back in to place.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "Iran has powerful incentives to keep its commitments." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "This deal shuts off the type of covert program Iran has pursued in the past.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "In July, we reached a comprehensive plan of action that meets our objectives." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "What was once proclaimed as a historic mistake is now held up as a success." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: â€œThe progress of Iran's nuclear program was halted for the first time in a decade.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "It was diplomacy that ratcheted up the pressure on Iran." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "Winning this global buy-in was not easy. I know. I was there." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "What made our new approach more effective was our ability to draw upon new U.N. Security Council resolutions." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: â€œIt was our very willingness to negotiate that helped America rally the world to our cause.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "I have also made clear my preference for a peaceful diplomatic resolution of the issue." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "Even before taking office, I made clear that Iran would not be allowed to acquire a nuclear weapon on my watch." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "The question then is not whether to prevent Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon, but how." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "Now more than ever, we need clear thinking in our foreign policy." â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: â€œMore than a decade later, we still live with the consequences of the decision to invade Iraq.â€ â€”President Obama #IranDeal

author: BarackObama
content: "If we keep taking steps toward a more perfect union ... America will move forward. There's nothing we can't do." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "We cannot ignore the problems that we have, but we can't stop running the race." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "We are not perfect, but we have the capacity to be more perfectâ€”mile after mile, step after step." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Justice and redemption go hand in hand." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Justice is living up to the common creed that I am my brother's keeper and I am my sister's keeper." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Justice is making sure that every young person knows that they are special and their lives matter." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Justice is not only the absence of oppressionâ€”it is the presence of opportunity." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Let's reward prisoners with reduced sentences if they complete programs that make them less likely to repeat an offense." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "I've asked my Attorney General to start a review of the overuse of solitary confinement in our federal prisons." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "We should not tolerate conditions in prison that have no place in any civilized country." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "On Thursday, I will be the first sitting president to visit a federal prison." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "We should pass a sentencing reform bill through congress this year." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "For nonviolent drug crimes, we need to lower long mandatory minimum sentencesâ€”or get rid of them entirely." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Don't just tag them as future criminals. Reach out to them as future citizens." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "We have to restore trust between our police and some of the communities where they serve." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "We gotta make sure boys and girls in those communities are loved and cherished and nurtured and invested in." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "What doesn't make sense is treating entire neighborhoods as danger zones." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "We recognize that every child deserves opportunity. Not just some. Not just our own." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "One study found that for every dollar we invest in Pre-K, we save at least twice that in reduced crime." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "If we make investments early in our children, we will reduce the need to incarcerate those kids." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "I believe crime is like any other epidemicâ€”we need to stop it before it starts." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "For the first time in 40 years, America's crime rate and incarceration rate went down at the same time." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "This is a cause that is bringing people in both houses of Congress together." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Mass incarceration makes our country worse offâ€”and we need to do something about it." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Our criminal justice system isn't as smart as it should be." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Our nation is being robbed of men and women who could be workers and taxpayers." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Around one million fathers are behind bars. Around one in nine African-American kids has a parent in prison." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "African Americans are more likely to be arrested. They are more likely to be sentenced to more time for the same crime." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "A growing body of research shows that people of color are more likely to be frisked, stopped, questioned, detained." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "African Americans and Latinos make up 30 percent of our population. They make up 60 percent of our inmates." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Roughly one-third of the Justice Department's budget now goes toward incarceration." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "For $80 billion we could double the salary of every high school teacher in America." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Every year, we spend $80 billion to keep those folks incarcerated." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "In far too many cases the punishment does not fit the crime." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "Over the last few decades, we've locked up more and more nonviolent drug offenders for longer than ever before." â€”President Obama

author: BarackObama
content: "If we're going to deal with this problem, and the inequities involved, we're going to have to speak honestly." â€”President Obama
